      section\par
         h1 Creating and Opening Presentations\par
            \par
      section\par
         h2 To create a new presentation:\par
         p\par
           img(src="images/create/create1.png")\par
           li Select the File tab to go to Backstage view.\par
           li Select New on the left side of the window, then click Blank Presentation or choose a theme.\par
           li A new presentation will appear.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          img(src="images/create/create2.png")\par
      section\par
         h2 To open an existing presentation:\par
         p\par
           li Select the File tab to go to Backstage view.\par
           li Select Open.\par
         img(src="images/create/create3.png")\par
       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Select Computer, then click Browse. Alternatively, you can choose OneDrive (previously known as SkyDrive) to open files stored on your OneDrive.\par
           img(src="images/create/create4.png")\par
       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The Open dialog box will appear. Locate and select your presentation, then click Open.\par
           img(src="images/create/create5.png")\par
\par
      section\par
         h2 To create a new presentation from a template:\par
         p\par
           li Click the File tab to access Backstage view.\par
           li Select New. You can click a suggested search to find templates or use the search bar to find something more specific. In our example, we'll search for Business presentations.\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           img(src="images/create/create7.png")\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Select a template to review it.\par
              img(src="images/create/create8.jpg")\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li A preview of the template will appear, along with additional information on how the template can be used.\par
           li Click Create to use the selected template.\par
           li A new presentation will appear with the selected template.\par
           img(src="images/create/create9.png")\par
      \par
      section\par
         h1 Save your Presentation\par
      \par
      section\par
         h2 Save File\par
         ul\par
           li PowerPoint offers two ways to save a file: Save and Save As. \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Save: When you create or edit a presentation, you'll use the Save command to save your changes. You'll use this command most of the time.\par
           li Save As: You'll use this command to create a copy of a presentation while keeping the original.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
         h2 To save a presentation:\par
         ul\par
           li You'll also need to pay close attention to where you save the presentation so it will be easy to find later.\par
         p\par
           li Locate and select the Save command on the Quick Access Toolbar.\par
            img(src="images/save/save1.png")\par
           li If you're saving the file for the first time, the Save As pane will appear in Backstage view.\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li To save the presentation to your computer, select Computer, then click Browse. Alternatively, you can click OneDrive to save the file to your OneDrive.\par
             img(src="images/save/save2.png")\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The Save As dialog box will appear. Select the location where you wish to save the presentation.\par
           li Enter a file name for the presentation, then click Save.\par
             img(src="images/save/save3.png")\par
\par
      section\par
          li The presentation will be saved. You can click the Save command again to save your changes as you modify the presentation.\par
          li You can also access the Save command by pressing CTRL+S on your keyboard\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
        h1 Slide Basics\par
      \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
        h3 To insert a new slide:\par
           li From the Home tab, click the bottom half of the New Slide command.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s3.png")\par
      \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Choose the desired slide layout from the menu that appears.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s6.png")\par
      \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The new slide will appear. Click any placeholder and begin typing to add text. You can also click an icon to add other types of content, like a picture or a chart.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s5.png")\par
      \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           h3 To copy and paste slides:\par
               li Select the slide you wish to copy in the Slide Navigation pane, then click the Copy command on the Home tab.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s8.png")\par
      \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li In the Slide Navigation pane, click just below a slide (or between two slides) to choose a paste location. A horizontal insertion point will appear.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s9.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Click the Paste command on the Home tab.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s10.png")\par
     \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The slide will appear in the selected location.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s11.png")\par
      \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           h2 Customizing slides\par
           h3 To format the slide background:\par
            p\par
              li Select the Design tab, then click the Format Background command.\par
              img(src="images/slide/s13.png")\par
     \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The Format Background pane will appear on the right. Select the desired fill options. In our example, we'll use a Solid fill with a light gold color.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s14.png") \par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The background style of the selected slide will update.\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li If desired, you can click Apply to All to apply the same background style to all slides in your presentation.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s15.jpg")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic') \par
           h3 To apply a theme: \par
     \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Select the Design tab on the Ribbon, then click the More drop-down arrow to see all of the available themes.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s16.png")\par
 \par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li Select the desired theme.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s17.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
           li The theme will be applied to your entire presentation.\par
           img(src="images/slide/s18.png")\par
\par
      section\par
          h2 To select text:\par
          li Before you can move or arrange text, you'll need to select it.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li Click next to the text you wish to select, drag the mouse over the text, then release your mouse. The text will be selected.\par
          img(src="images/text/text1.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h1 Copying and moving text\par
          li PowerPoint allows you to copy text that is already on a slide and paste it elsewhere, which can save you time. If you wish to move text, you can cut and paste or drag and drop the text.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h2 To copy and paste text:\par
          li Select the text you wish to copy, then click the Copy command on the Home tab.\par
          img(src="images/text/text2.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li Place the insertion point where you wish the text to appear.\par
          li Click the Paste command on the Home tab.\par
          img(src="images/text/text3.png")\par
          li The copied text will appear.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h2 To cut and paste text:\par
          li Select the text you wish to move, then click the Cut command.\par
          img(src="images/text/text4.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li Place the insertion point where you wish the text to appear, then click the Paste command.\par
          img(src="images/text/text5.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li The text will appear in the new location.\par
          li You can access the cut, copy, and paste commands by using keyboard shortcuts. Press Ctrl+X to cut, Ctrl+C to copy, and Ctrl+V to paste.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h1 Find and Replace\par
          li When you're working with longer presentations, it can be difficult and time consuming to locate a specific word or phrase. PowerPoint can automatically search your presentation using the Find feature, and it allows you to quickly change words or phrases using the Replace feature.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h2 To find text:\par
          li In our example, we'll use the Find feature to look for specific dog breeds in our presentation.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li From the Home tab, click the Find command.\par
          img(src="images/text/find1.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li A dialog box will appear. Enter the text you wish to find in the Find what: field, then click Find Next.\par
          img(src="images/text/find2.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li If the text is found, it will be selected.\par
          img(src="images/text/find3.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li Click Find Next to find further instances. If none are found, a dialog box will appear. Click OK.\par
          img(src="images/text/find4.png")\par
          li When you are finished, click Close to exit the dialog box.\par
          li You can also access the Find command by pressing Ctrl+F on your keyboard.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h2 To replace text:\par
          li At times, you may discover that you've repeatedly made a mistake throughout your presentation (such as misspelling someone's name), or that you need to exchange a particular word or phrase for another. You can use the Replace feature to make quick revisions. In our example, we'll replace with word "pounds" with the abbreviation "lbs."\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li From the Home tab, click the Replace command.\par
          img(src="images/text/find5.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li A dialog box will appear. Type the text you wish to find in the Find what: field.\par
          li Type the text you wish to replace it with in the Replace with: field, then click Find Next.\par
          img(src="images/text/find6.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li If the text is found, it will be selected. Review the text to make sure you want to replace it.\par
          li If you wish to replace it, select one of the replace options. Replace will replace individual instances, and Replace All will replace every instance. In our example, we'll use the Replace option.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          img(src="images/text/find7.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li The selected text will be replaced.\par
          img(src="images/text/find8.png")\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li You'll need to be careful when using the Replace All option. In the example below, changing the word "Pounds" to "lbs." would have been incorrect in this context. You can click Find Next to skip to the next instance without replacing the text.\par
\par
      section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          h2. Theme elements\par
          p Every PowerPoint theme, including the default Office theme, has its own theme elements. Those elements are: \par
          li Theme Colors: There are 10 theme colors, along with darker and lighter variations, available from every Color menu.\par
          img(src="images/applytheme/theme_understand_color.png")\par
\pard       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
\pard           li Theme Fonts: There are two theme fonts available at the top of the Font menu under Theme Fonts.\par
          img(src="images/applytheme/theme_understand_font.png")\par
\pard       section.emphatic-text(data-bespoke-backdrop='emphatic')\par
          li Theme Effects: These affect the preset shape styles. You can find shape styles on the Format tab whenever you select a shape or SmartArt graphic.\par
\pard           img(src="images/applytheme/theme_element_effect.png")\par
          \par
